147
00:08:33.564 --> 00:08:34.595
So as you know,

148
00:08:35.744 --> 00:08:39.624
smoking is a leading cause of cancer mortality with

149
00:08:39.725 --> 00:08:43.004
over 30%, particularly lung cancer with

150
00:08:43.105 --> 00:08:44.444
over 80%.

151
00:08:45.424 --> 00:08:49.284
And thanks to the advance of the smoking

152
00:08:49.344 --> 00:08:52.304
cessation program, the number of the

153
00:08:53.524 --> 00:08:57.384
former smokers will double that of the current smokers in the United States.

154
00:08:58.204 --> 00:09:02.104
However, former smokers remain at the higher risk of

155
00:09:02.144 --> 00:09:05.264
the different kind of cancer, particularly lung cancer.

156
00:09:06.024 --> 00:09:09.884
And the previous study indicates that the protein can capture the

157
00:09:09.904 --> 00:09:12.534
