00:21:53.532 --> 00:21:57.452
present our work on the adult height and prostate cancer risk in the

373
00:21:57.512 --> 00:21:59.472
Health Professional Follow-Up Study.

374
00:22:00.972 --> 00:22:02.412
I have nothing to disclose.

375
00:22:03.852 --> 00:22:07.812
So growing evidence has suggested that taller height might be

376
00:22:07.872 --> 00:22:11.372
a risk factor for prostate cancer, especially for

377
00:22:11.392 --> 00:22:13.312
advanced or fatal prostate cancer.

378
00:22:14.032 --> 00:22:17.292
Here on the right, the table summarize results from the pooled

379
00:22:17.332 --> 00:22:21.312
analysis of 15 cohort studies. And you can see that

380
00:22:21.452 --> 00:22:25.412
men of taller height are at a slight increased risk of total

381
00:22:25.452 --> 00:22:28.572
prostate cancer with a borderline significance.

382
00:22:29.412 --> 00:22:33.212
But when we stratify by subtype, the association

383
00:22:33.292 --> 00:22:36.792
is stronger for advanced and fatal prostate cancer

384
00:22:37.252 --> 00:22:38.952
than with localized prostate cancer.

385
00:22:39.892 --> 00:22:43.532
However, the biologic basis underlying this association

386
00:22:43.592 --> 00:22:47.392
remains unclear. So we know that height is

387
00:22:47.432 --> 00:22:50.772
shaped by both genetic factors and early life

388
00:22:50.932 --> 00:22:54.732
exposures, and both of which can influence the risk of prostate

389
00:22:54.812 --> 00:22:58.072
cancer. For example, puberty is a crucial

390
00:22:58.152 --> 00:22:59.492
developmental period

391
00:23:00.312 --> 00:23:00.712
that can

392
00:23:01.932 --> 00:23:05.252
affect both height growth and prostate

393
00:23:05.552 --> 00:23:07.292
growth and development.

394
00:23:08.192 --> 00:23:11.652
So exposure during this period may

395
00:23:12.492 --> 00:23:15.512
have impacts on prostate cancer risk later in life.

396
00:23:16.592 --> 00:23:19.992
So this raises the question whether height in this

397
00:23:20.052 --> 00:23:24.032
context primarily reflect the genetic

398
00:23:24.072 --> 00:23:27.792
factors, early life influences, or a combination of both.

399
00:23:32.172 --> 00:23:35.792
So to address this question, we use the Health Professional Follow-Up Study,

400
00:23:36.332 --> 00:23:39.832
which is a prospective cohort that enrolled more than

401
00:23:39.912 --> 00:23:43.812
51,000 men at baseline. And during follow-up,

402
00:23:45.112 --> 00:23:49.092
a subset of the participants donated their blood or cheek samples

403
00:23:49.592 --> 00:23:52.752
that allowed us to have their DNA information.

404
00:23:53.292 --> 00:23:57.052
And also among men diagnosed with prostate cancer, we were able to

405
00:23:57.092 --> 00:24:00.232
obtain their tumor tissue that allows us to

406
00:24:00.932 --> 00:24:02.632
have their molecular profiling.

407
00:24:03.692 --> 00:24:07.092
So under this rich resource, we conducted three

408
00:24:07.192 --> 00:24:08.572
complementary analysis.

409
00:24:09.512 --> 00:24:13.472
First, in the cohort analysis, with up to 34 year

410
00:24:13.532 --> 00:24:14.132
of follow-up,

411
00:24:15.072 --> 00:24:18.811
we further confirmed the association of height

412
00:24:19.132 --> 00:24:20.292
and prostate cancer risk.

413
00:24:21.132 --> 00:24:24.862
And second, in the genetic decomposition analysis, we try

414
00:24:25.032 --> 00:24:28.812
to separate the genetic from the non-genetic component

415
00:24:29.212 --> 00:24:31.782
of height.And third,

416
00:24:32.722 --> 00:24:34.902
using transcriptomic profiling,

417
00:24:35.822 --> 00:24:39.682
we try to identify molecular features in the tumor that is

418
00:24:39.762 --> 00:24:41.282
also associated with height.

419
00:24:43.702 --> 00:24:46.342
So here shows the results from the cohort analysis.

420
00:24:46.702 --> 00:24:50.592
As expected, we see that taller height is strongly

421
00:24:50.642 --> 00:24:54.402
and positively associated with risk of fatal prostate cancer, but

422
00:24:54.462 --> 00:24:57.902
show little association with total prostate cancer,

423
00:24:58.462 --> 00:25:01.942
which is consistent with previous findings.

424
00:25:03.962 --> 00:25:07.642
And next, we try to separate the

425
00:25:08.362 --> 00:25:12.071
two major contributors to height, the inherited

426
00:25:12.162 --> 00:25:15.822
genetic factors, represented by a whole

427
00:25:15.882 --> 00:25:19.582
genome PRS of height, and the early life nutritional

428
00:25:19.662 --> 00:25:23.602
factors represented by adolescent dairy or milk

429
00:25:23.662 --> 00:25:27.522
intake, which has been previously shown to be a strong

430
00:25:27.582 --> 00:25:28.762
predictor of height.

431
00:25:31.022 --> 00:25:33.702
So here the assumption is both either

432
00:25:34.662 --> 00:25:38.642
components may contribute to height and may therefore, through

433
00:25:38.682 --> 00:25:42.662
certain biologic pathways, increase the risk of fatal prostate cancer.

434
00:25:44.742 --> 00:25:48.692
So here to separate the components, we used a residual approach.

435
00:25:49.242 --> 00:25:53.122
So specifically, we first regressed the observed height

436
00:25:53.162 --> 00:25:55.962
on the height PRS and derived a residual.

437
00:25:56.422 --> 00:26:00.302
So here the residual represents a proportion of height that cannot be

438
00:26:00.342 --> 00:26:01.772
explained by genetics.

439
00:26:02.882 --> 00:26:06.702
We then related this residual factor to fatal prostate

440
00:26:06.742 --> 00:26:10.652
cancer risk and to see how much the association would

441
00:26:10.662 --> 00:26:14.222
be attenuated compared to the total effect of height.

442
00:26:16.902 --> 00:26:18.282
So, here the

443
00:26:19.122 --> 00:26:22.482
rationale is that if the association would

444
00:26:22.542 --> 00:26:26.522
be substantially attenuated, then genetics might

445
00:26:26.562 --> 00:26:30.132
explain most of the observed association with

446
00:26:30.202 --> 00:26:34.142
height. And similarly, we conducted the residual

447
00:26:34.162 --> 00:26:37.702
approach for dairy intake and to compare the

448
00:26:37.782 --> 00:26:41.641
association with fatal prostate cancer and see how much the

449
00:26:41.651 --> 00:26:43.502
association would be attenuated.

450
00:26:45.382 --> 00:26:49.162
So this part of the analysis was led by our master's

451
00:26:49.202 --> 00:26:50.342
student, Diane Fu.

452
00:26:51.662 --> 00:26:55.262
In the genetic residual analysis, we're limited to

453
00:26:56.142 --> 00:26:59.062
participants whose genetic information is available.

454
00:26:59.472 --> 00:27:03.382
And in the subset of cohort, we still see that height

455
00:27:03.422 --> 00:27:06.202
is positively associated with fatal prostate cancer,

456
00:27:07.122 --> 00:27:10.942
although we might be underpowered to detect a significance.

457
00:27:12.222 --> 00:27:15.762
And similarly, we see the PRS of height showed a

458
00:27:15.842 --> 00:27:19.602
similar magnitude of association with fatal prostate cancer,

459
00:27:20.222 --> 00:27:23.742
but the residual of height after accounted for the PRS,

460
00:27:24.182 --> 00:27:27.741
showed essentially no association, which means the

461
00:27:27.782 --> 00:27:31.502
association was largely attenuated after

462
00:27:31.512 --> 00:27:33.122
accounting for the PRS.

463
00:27:35.462 --> 00:27:39.172
And in the dairy residual analysis, again, we saw a

464
00:27:39.262 --> 00:27:43.182
strong positive association for total height.

465
00:27:43.862 --> 00:27:47.822
But after accounting for teenage dairy or milk intake,

466
00:27:48.262 --> 00:27:51.842
the residual of height still showed positive

467
00:27:51.922 --> 00:27:54.902
association with fatal prostate cancer.

468
00:27:55.082 --> 00:27:56.282
So there's little

469
00:27:57.282 --> 00:28:01.102
level of attenuation after accounted for teenage

470
00:28:01.112 --> 00:28:04.882
dairy or milk intake. So taking together the evidence from

471
00:28:04.922 --> 00:28:07.792
both the genetic and dairy residual analysis,

472
00:28:08.702 --> 00:28:12.462
we conclude that here, the association between

473
00:28:12.802 --> 00:28:16.642
