00:50:03.018 --> 00:50:05.498
maybe you have said this, but I missed.

848
00:50:05.838 --> 00:50:09.498
Are there differences in the clusters based on copy number

849
00:50:09.738 --> 00:50:11.428
between Black and White patients?

850
00:50:12.408 --> 00:50:16.098
So in terms of each cluster, we don't see any

851
00:50:16.138 --> 00:50:19.698
necessarily differences in terms of cluster membership by race.

852
00:50:19.738 --> 00:50:23.538
However, when we look at overall survival, we did find that there is a

853
00:50:23.578 --> 00:50:27.178
significant difference between Black and White women in the third cluster.

854
00:50:27.278 --> 00:50:29.108
So that's specifically within that cluster.

855
00:50:29.118 --> 00:50:32.518
And that was the gain dominant, so within a cluster that has a lot of gains.

856
00:50:33.018 --> 00:50:34.818
Thank you. We have a... Yeah, go ahead.

857
00:50:34.878 --> 00:50:35.078
Sure.

858
00:50:35.518 --> 00:50:35.528
Yes.

859
00:50:35.558 --> 00:50:38.438
Paul Sheet, MD Anderson. Thanks. That was a really interesting talk.

860
00:50:38.518 --> 00:50:39.438
Thanks.

861
00:50:39.858 --> 00:50:43.698
I'm a little more used to certain cancers showing chromosome-specific

862
00:50:44.038 --> 00:50:46.238
patterns like you showed with chromosome eight, for example,

