00:50:47.158 --> 00:50:51.038
and not so much necessarily just genome-wide gains and losses, but

864
00:50:51.078 --> 00:50:54.258
maybe that exists in other cancers as well. So that's one interesting.

865
00:50:54.318 --> 00:50:54.658
Two,

866
00:50:56.038 --> 00:50:59.878
would genome-wide

867
00:50:59.918 --> 00:51:03.878
hypomethylation or hypermethylation ever show up something that

868
00:51:03.918 --> 00:51:07.468
would... Would it ever demonstrate something like in genome-wide gains and

869
00:51:07.518 --> 00:51:11.258
losses, or would they show distinct patterns from

870
00:51:11.378 --> 00:51:12.038
CNAs?

871
00:51:12.558 --> 00:51:14.358
So yes. Are you asking if

872
00:51:15.658 --> 00:51:19.238
any kind of distinct differential methylation that's occurring across a

873
00:51:19.278 --> 00:51:20.498
genome, if that would be

874
00:51:21.518 --> 00:51:23.778
correlated to the copy number alteration that we're seeing?

875
00:51:24.358 --> 00:51:26.878
Yeah. Not correlated so much, but yeah.

876
00:51:27.118 --> 00:51:28.518
Would it look like that ever? I

877
00:51:29.458 --> 00:51:32.638
don't know exactly how you were able to make that distinction

878
00:51:32.678 --> 00:51:33.458
between

879
00:51:34.678 --> 00:51:38.398
large-scale hypermethylation or hypomethylation

880
00:51:38.718 --> 00:51:42.618
and one of the distinct CNAs. I think your findings are robust because the proof is

881
00:51:42.658 --> 00:51:46.478
in the pudding based on what you relate them to afterwards in

882
00:51:46.518 --> 00:51:49.218
terms of the clinical outcomes and so forth.

883
00:51:49.458 --> 00:51:53.438
Yeah. So I think one of the benefits of our approach, which uses specifically

884
00:51:53.478 --> 00:51:57.358
the methylation array data for copy number calling, is that you

885
00:51:57.398 --> 00:52:01.178
can also analyze the methylation data separately because they

886
00:52:01.238 --> 00:52:05.178
are different approaches. So I wouldn't necessarily be able

887
00:52:05.298 --> 00:52:09.118
to assess differential methylation based off of this copy number

888
00:52:09.198 --> 00:52:13.078
calling, but I could have kind of additional analyses focused

889
00:52:13.418 --> 00:52:15.618
on identifying any differential methylation.

890
00:52:16.078 --> 00:52:19.458
I do believe and feel that in this

891
00:52:19.478 --> 00:52:21.918
specific space, that these are distinct.

892
00:52:22.398 --> 00:52:25.798
So I wouldn't necessarily say that a region that shows a lot of

893
00:52:26.378 --> 00:52:28.858
hypermethylation would necessarily be

894
00:52:30.258 --> 00:52:34.118
associated or kind of giving us insight into why we have these regions of copy

895
00:52:34.158 --> 00:52:34.738
number calling.

896
00:52:36.578 --> 00:52:36.938
Thank you.

897
00:52:40.418 --> 00:52:40.858
Thank you.

898
00:52:43.838 --> 00:52:46.858
I'd like to invite our next speaker, Brett Reid.

899
00:52:57.018 --> 00:53:00.508
Good afternoon. I'm Brett Reid from Moffitt Cancer Center, and today I'm going to

900
00:53:00.578 --> 00:53:04.438
be presenting a study that will demonstrate that the spatial context of T cell

901
00:53:04.478 --> 00:53:08.438
infiltration and exhaustion is an important determinant of ovarian

902
00:53:08.498 --> 00:53:10.138
cancer survival in Black women.

903
00:53:13.318 --> 00:53:17.038
As we just heard from Irma, epithelial ovarian cancer is one of the most lethal

904
00:53:17.058 --> 00:53:20.958
gynecologic cancers, with only about half of women

905
00:53:21.058 --> 00:53:23.437
surviving five years post-diagnosis.

906
00:53:24.198 --> 00:53:26.008
And the survival rates and

907
00:53:27.818 --> 00:53:30.698
trends are worse among Black women.

908
00:53:32.398 --> 00:53:35.978
So one of the strongest prognostic factors for ovarian

909
00:53:36.078 --> 00:53:39.878
cancer is the presence of intratumoral T cells, particularly the

910
00:53:39.918 --> 00:53:43.198
CD8 positive cytotoxic T cells.

911
00:53:43.618 --> 00:53:46.218
However, this association varies by race.

912
00:53:46.638 --> 00:53:50.618
So in a prior study, the survival benefit, the

913
00:53:50.678 --> 00:53:54.038
same survival benefit that we saw in White women was not

914
00:53:54.098 --> 00:53:57.758
observed in Black women, even though they had the same

915
00:53:57.818 --> 00:54:01.618
levels of T cell infiltration. And this raises the possibility

916
00:54:01.658 --> 00:54:02.098
that

917
00:54:02.998 --> 00:54:06.598
T cell infiltration alone is not fully capturing the relevant

918
00:54:06.638 --> 00:54:10.618
biology of the tumor immune microenvironment in this population.

919
00:54:12.398 --> 00:54:16.278
So given this, the objective of our study was to more fully

920
00:54:16.338 --> 00:54:20.038
characterize the tumor immune microenvironment in Black

921
00:54:20.118 --> 00:54:23.438
women and identify the phenotypes that are associated with survival.

922
00:54:24.678 --> 00:54:28.418
We focused on two key features: the T cell functional state and the

923
00:54:28.518 --> 00:54:30.578
spatial localization of those T cells.

924
00:54:31.998 --> 00:54:35.098
To characterize function, we assessed the

925
00:54:35.538 --> 00:54:39.218
exhaustion state, which is a state that arises under persistent

926
00:54:39.298 --> 00:54:40.338
antigen exposure

927
00:54:41.278 --> 00:54:45.088
with the upregulation of inhibitory receptors including TIM3 and

928
00:54:45.178 --> 00:54:48.568
PD-1. And these cells exhibit reduced cytotoxic

929
00:54:48.658 --> 00:54:50.938
activity and proliferative capacity.

930
00:54:51.678 --> 00:54:55.498
Now, in parallel, we also characterized the localization of these T cells.

931
00:54:56.738 --> 00:55:00.038
So ovarian tumors have significant tissue heterogeneity

932
00:55:00.098 --> 00:55:03.654
withStromal infiltration throughout the tumor,

933
00:55:04.194 --> 00:55:05.134
and importantly,

934
00:55:06.234 --> 00:55:10.194
where the lymphocytes are located in these regions have shown differences in

935
00:55:10.214 --> 00:55:13.924
their activity, cytokine signaling, and even the transcriptional

936
00:55:14.034 --> 00:55:14.734
programs.

937
00:55:16.294 --> 00:55:18.774
So this supports that these regions

938
00:55:19.674 --> 00:55:22.254
are distinct immune contexts for these cells.

939
00:55:24.004 --> 00:55:27.974
So therefore, our hypothesis was that both the functional state

940
00:55:28.054 --> 00:55:31.854
and the spatial localization of T cells may be more significant determinants of

941
00:55:31.914 --> 00:55:33.254
survival for Black women.

942
00:55:35.214 --> 00:55:38.074
To evaluate this, we utilized whole tissue sections

943
00:55:39.994 --> 00:55:43.834
from primary chemo-naive ovarian tumors, and the

944
00:55:43.934 --> 00:55:47.843
FFPE sections underwent multiplex immunofluorescence, and the

945
00:55:47.914 --> 00:55:51.074
markers included CD3 to identify the T cells,

946
00:55:51.614 --> 00:55:55.374
CD8 to identify cytotoxic T cells, and then for

947
00:55:55.654 --> 00:55:59.374
exhaustion, we included the inhibitory receptors TIM-3 and PD-1.

948
00:56:00.934 --> 00:56:04.734
Spatial localization was quantified using a compartmental approach,

949
00:56:05.434 --> 00:56:09.134
where cell coordinates were used to generate smooth point pattern

950
00:56:09.174 --> 00:56:11.174
intensities for the tumor and stroma.

951
00:56:12.074 --> 00:56:15.214
And we then excluded the mixed interface regions.

952
00:56:15.634 --> 00:56:19.334
And this resulted in more homogeneous, spatially resolved

953
00:56:19.374 --> 00:56:21.854
tumor and stroma compartments for our analysis.

954
00:56:24.734 --> 00:56:28.594
The resulting measures included compartment-specific T cell and subpopulation

955
00:56:28.694 --> 00:56:32.194
proportions, which were analyzed using Cox proportional hazards

956
00:56:32.254 --> 00:56:36.074
regression. And to build the models, we used a hierarchical modeling

957
00:56:36.134 --> 00:56:40.074
approach where we decomposed the immune response into

958
00:56:40.134 --> 00:56:42.454
three biologically distinct components.

959
00:56:43.034 --> 00:56:46.374
So first, we modeled a term for the extent of T cell infiltration,

960
00:56:46.854 --> 00:56:50.674
which was the ratio of CD3 positive to CD3

961
00:56:50.734 --> 00:56:51.314
negative

962
00:56:53.294 --> 00:56:53.814
proportions.

963
00:56:55.434 --> 00:56:59.254
Okay. And then next, we modeled the composition

964
00:56:59.354 --> 00:57:00.294
of the T cells,

965
00:57:01.094 --> 00:57:03.094
the cytotoxic composition of the T cells.

966
00:57:03.104 --> 00:57:03.934
So this was

967
00:57:04.754 --> 00:57:08.334
the CD8 positive to CD8 negative ratio in the

968
00:57:08.354 --> 00:57:12.013
CD3 positive cells. And this term captures the cytotoxic

969
00:57:12.054 --> 00:57:15.354
enrichment that is independent of the total T cell

970
00:57:15.394 --> 00:57:16.054
abundance.

971
00:57:16.914 --> 00:57:20.694
And third, we modeled the exhaustion within cytotoxic T cells using the

972
00:57:20.734 --> 00:57:24.654
TIM-3 positive to negative ratio in the subpopulation

973
00:57:24.694 --> 00:57:27.254
of CD3 positive and CD8 negative cells.

974
00:57:27.754 --> 00:57:31.214
And again, this captures the exhaustion effect that is independent of

975
00:57:31.254 --> 00:57:35.194
both the cytotoxic composition and also the total T

976
00:57:35.274 --> 00:57:39.004
cell abundance. And so together, this model allows us to

977
00:57:39.014 --> 00:57:41.054
distinguish if survival

978
00:57:42.434 --> 00:57:46.374
is driven by how many T cells are present, what type they

979
00:57:46.454 --> 00:57:49.974
are, and whether they're functionally engaged all in the same model.

980
00:57:50.384 --> 00:57:53.514
And our models were adjusted for batch and clinical factors.

981
00:57:55.814 --> 00:57:59.614
In total, there were 221 Black women from the ACES

982
00:57:59.674 --> 00:58:03.574
study that were included in our analysis, and most

983
00:58:03.614 --> 00:58:07.254
had high-grade serous subtype and were of advanced stage

984
00:58:07.334 --> 00:58:07.854
disease.

985
00:58:09.814 --> 00:58:13.234
The whole tissue sections, half

986
00:58:13.874 --> 00:58:17.614
of the samples had one million or more cells, and

987
00:58:17.694 --> 00:58:21.554
this is exponentially larger than, say, the tissue microarray cores that

988
00:58:21.594 --> 00:58:25.414
we've more typically seen in these studies, which have 5,000 to 10,000 cells on

989
00:58:25.474 --> 00:58:27.914
average. So it's much larger.

990
00:58:29.154 --> 00:58:29.374
In the

991
00:58:30.334 --> 00:58:31.534
tumor region, the

992
00:58:32.794 --> 00:58:34.234
median T cell proportion was

993
00:58:36.514 --> 00:58:40.274
2% or higher, and this was two times higher in the stroma regions.

994
00:58:40.594 --> 00:58:44.454
Now, of these T cells, 30% in the tumor region were

995
00:58:44.494 --> 00:58:48.053
cytotoxic, and of the cytotoxic T

996
00:58:48.154 --> 00:58:51.874
cells, 3% had the TIM-3 marker, and less than

997
00:58:52.074 --> 00:58:55.474
1% co-expressed both the TIM-3 and PD-1 marker.

998
00:58:56.834 --> 00:58:57.414
And these

999
00:58:58.354 --> 00:59:02.094
exhausted and cytotoxic proportions were slightly

1000
00:59:02.174 --> 00:59:03.594
lower in the stroma regions.

1001
00:59:06.754 --> 00:59:10.254
And when we modeled the immune features for the tumor and stroma separately using

1002
00:59:10.314 --> 00:59:14.014
stratified models, we didn't see any significant associations with survival.

1003
00:59:14.614 --> 00:59:18.454
However, when they were both modeled together in a combined model, we then see that

1004
00:59:18.514 --> 00:59:22.494
higher cytotoxic T cells in

1005
00:59:22.514 --> 00:59:26.344
the tumor are associated with better survival, whereas when in

1006
00:59:26.374 --> 00:59:28.594
the stroma, they're associated with worse survival.

1007
00:59:29.974 --> 00:59:33.414
So given these opposing effects, we next looked at the difference between the

1008
00:59:33.454 --> 00:59:36.934
cytotoxic T cell enrichment in the tumor and stroma using a

1009
00:59:36.974 --> 00:59:38.014
gradient metric.

1010
00:59:39.714 --> 00:59:43.574
And we found that this metric was associated with survival, where if

1011
00:59:44.334 --> 00:59:48.134
cytotoxic T cell enrichment in the tumor was higher relevant to the

1012
00:59:48.194 --> 00:59:51.034
stroma, we see better survival.

1013
00:59:51.944 --> 00:59:55.634
And another way to look at this that may be a little more intuitive is to

1014
00:59:55.714 --> 00:59:59.534
categorize this gradient into whether the cytotoxic T cells are higher in

1015
00:59:59.574 --> 01:00:03.504
the tumor versus in the stroma. And so looking at this

1016
01:00:03.534 --> 01:00:06.894
distribution of the gradient metric, we used a one and a half fold

1017
01:00:07.014 --> 01:00:09.914
threshold where tumor stroma

1018
01:00:10.034 --> 01:00:13.934
cytotoxic T cell enrichments that were within 50%

1019
01:00:13.994 --> 01:00:16.934
of each other were classified as equivalent.

1020
01:00:17.394 --> 01:00:21.254
Whereas if it was 50% higher or more in the tumor, it was

1021
01:00:21.294 --> 01:00:24.974
tumor dominant, and then vice versa for the stroma, being

1022
01:00:25.074 --> 01:00:25.854
stroma dominant.

1023
01:00:26.874 --> 01:00:29.874
And we see that 50% of tumors were tumor dominant.

1024
01:00:31.594 --> 01:00:35.084
When we looked at survival in these groups, we see that the

1025
01:00:35.114 --> 01:00:38.754
tumor-dominant cytotoxic T cell enrichment is associated with better

1026
01:00:38.774 --> 01:00:39.294
survival.

1027
01:00:41.574 --> 01:00:42.294
Now, a

1028
01:00:43.274 --> 01:00:47.234
helpful exercise is to visualize these immunotypes

1029
01:00:47.394 --> 01:00:50.584
across different T cell localization patterns.

1030
01:00:52.034 --> 01:00:52.854
So here I have

1031
01:00:53.654 --> 01:00:57.454
three samples, and in the first sample where T cells are

1032
01:00:57.494 --> 01:01:01.254
confined to the stroma region, in standard terminology, we would typically call

1033
01:01:01.274 --> 01:01:04.994
this immune excluded, whereas the other two would be immune infiltrated.

